between-text.description: Text is any copy that isn’t using a display style. It’s built into our text styles, but you’ll need to add it in when they’re not in the same block of content.

image-bottom.description: Our assets contain built in padding, but sometimes require a little bit of extra breathing room.

h1.description: Used for the main screen title, should be used only once per screen. It pairs with large body.

h2.description: Handy for dividing your screen into sections. It pairs perfectly with large body.

h3.description: Designed for sections within sections to increase the information hierarchy.

h4.description: Perfect for large amounts of content. Pairs with large body and default body.

p1.description:
Emphasises and highlights important words or small titles. It’s used in expressive components,
such as buttons and links.

p2.description: Used for for paragraphs. Pairs with screen title and section title.

p3-400.description: Mainly tables. When you need something a little smaller than large, or to compliment large body.
